					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I'm a little surprised that the number 149 works out correctly. If that's one byte per IRQ, that's a data rate of 12KB/sec... <br /><br />My understanding is that the entire 64KB of an FDS disk plays through in about 7.5 seconds (give or take), and that implies a data rate of about 9KB/sec....<br /><br />Regardless, I'd naively expect the correct number to be some integer multiple of 8 (or 16?) of 21.5MHz clock cycles from the crystal in the FDS.</div>

